<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta content='text/html; charset=UTF-8' http-equiv='Content-Type' />
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #333;
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
      }
      h1, h2, h3 {
        color: #0066cc;
      }
      .command {
        background-color: #f5f5f5;
        padding: 15px;
        border-radius: 5px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      .command h3 {
        margin-top: 0;
      }
      .steps {
        margin-left: 20px;
      }
      .footer {
        margin-top: 30px;
        padding-top: 15px;
        border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
        font-size: 0.8em;
        color: #666;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="content">
      <p>Hello <%= @email %>,</p>
      <p>Re: <%= @subject %></p>
      <h2>WELCOME TO POSTCARDMAILER.US!</h2>
    
    <p>Hello <%= @email %>,</p>
    
    <p>Thank you for requesting help with PostcardMailer.us. Below you'll find instructions for using our service through email commands.</p>
    
    <h2>Available Commands</h2>
    
    <div class="command">
      <h3>1. Sign Up</h3>
      <p>To create a new account:</p>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>Send an email to <strong>signup@postcardmailer.us</strong></li>
        <li>Include your <strong>full name</strong> in the subject line</li>
        <li>In the email body, include your complete mailing address (street, city, state, ZIP)</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Example:<br>
        To: signup@postcardmailer.us<br>
        Subject: John Smith<br>
        Body: 123 Main Street<br>
        San Francisco, CA 94110
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="command">
      <h3>2. Add an Address</h3>
      <p>To add a new address to your account:</p>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>Send an email to <strong>adduser@postcardmailer.us</strong></li>
        <li>Include a <strong>nickname</strong> for this address in the subject line</li>
        <li>In the email body, include the recipient's name and address</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Example:<br>
        To: adduser@postcardmailer.us<br>
        Subject: mom<br>
        Body: Jane Smith<br>
        456 Oak Avenue<br>
        Chicago, IL 60601
      </p>
      <p><em>Note: Our AI-powered address parser will automatically standardize and validate the address format to ensure accurate delivery through the US Postal Service.</em></p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="command">
      <h3>3. Send a Postcard</h3>
      <p>To send a postcard to someone in your address book:</p>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>Send an email to <strong>$nickname@postcardmailer.us</strong></li>
        <li>Use the subject line for the <strong>message</strong> to the recipient</li>
        <li>Attach the <strong>image</strong> you want to use for the postcard</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Example:<br>
        To: mom@postcardmailer.us<br>
        Subject: Had a great time in San Francisco!<br>
        Attachment: vacation-photo.jpg
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="command">
      <h3>4. Get Help</h3>
      <p>To receive these instructions again:</p>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>Send an email to <strong>help@postcardmailer.us</strong></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Important Notes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>New accounts require verification before you can send postcards</li>
      <li>Make sure addresses are complete and formatted correctly</li>
      <li>Image attachments should be clear and high resolution for best results</li>
      <li>The subject line is used to identify the recipient by their nickname</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p>If you have any other questions or need assistance, please reply to this email.</p>
    
    <div class="footer">
      <p>&copy; <%= Date.today.year %> PostcardMailer.us</p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html> 